data.title: EASTLAWN MEMORY GARDENS – MedinaCountyGraves.com
data.text:
TOWNSHIP: Brunswick Hills (City of Brunswick)

ALTERNATE NAMES: Eastlawn Memorial Gardens

LOCATION: north side of Grafton Rd. (CR-42); west of West 130th St. (CR-17)

ADDRESS: 2869 Grafton Rd.

CURRENT OWNER: American Cemetery Services LLP

ACCESS: public

STATUS: active

SIZE: 44.8152 total acres (not all developed yet for cemetery purposes)

ESTIMATED NUMBER OF BURIALS: 2642 (as of July 29, 2005)

EARLIEST KNOWN BURIAL: Floyd J. Culp who was interred November 5, 1965

MOST RECENT KNOWN BURIAL: still active

GPS:

003-18B-17-050 (Medina County Engineer’s Overhead View – rear undeveloped parcel)

ORIGINAL LOT #: Tract 2, Lot 35
